The basic reproduction number generally represented by R0 is a fundamental quantity in the study and analysis of mathematical models in epidemiology. R0 is commonly defined as the number of secondary cases that can be produced by one case of an infected individual in a completely susceptible population. The general framework for the determination of the basic reproduction number can be found in [15]. R0 is presented for different disease transmission models based on a system of differential equations. The expression of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
